00:02:46.666 --> 00:02:49.169
It's now... 2019.

00:02:49.269 --> 00:02:52.272
So that was eight years ago.

00:02:52.372 --> 00:02:55.608
So I'd sit here
and play here.

00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:58.645
♪♪♪

00:02:58.745 --> 00:03:01.214
Scooter: No one has ever
grown up in the history of

00:03:01.314 --> 00:03:02.281
humanity like Justin Bieber.

00:03:02.381 --> 00:03:04.717 line:0%
No one has ever been that
famous worldwide in an

00:03:04.817 --> 00:03:07.754 line:0%
era of social media where
every year of your adolescence

00:03:07.854 --> 00:03:09.489 line:0%
you were the most Googled
person on the planet.

00:03:09.589 --> 00:03:10.890
Justin: Oh, I went
to that school.

00:03:10.990 --> 00:03:14.427
Jumped the fence
one time there.

00:03:14.527 --> 00:03:16.896
Got suspended.

00:03:16.996 --> 00:03:19.699 line:0%
Hailey: You know, starting
out as a boy in front

00:03:19.799 --> 00:03:24.237 line:0%
of the entire world and
then transforming into

00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:27.840 line:0%
a young adult, a teenager,
and then like a young man,

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:30.343
and everybody's had to watch
him go through every single

00:03:30.443 --> 00:03:36.649
phase of life essentially from,
I don't know, 14, 15,

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:39.953
and now he's really an adult.

00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:41.721
Justin: So this is it.

00:03:41.821 --> 00:03:43.389
Hailey: Oh, yeah, I remember.

00:03:43.489 --> 00:03:44.958
Justin: This is like the
apartment I grew up in.

00:03:49.561 --> 00:03:50.730
Justin: Yeah-ha.

00:03:53.065 --> 00:03:54.968
I would have never thought
that in a million years.

00:03:58.437 --> 00:03:59.405
What up, man.

00:03:59.505 --> 00:04:00.573
- What's going on?

00:04:00.673 --> 00:04:02.342
Justin: How are you?

00:04:02.442 --> 00:04:04.310
Hailey: He has gone through so
much in the last three years,

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:06.512
four years since his
last album came out,

00:04:06.612 --> 00:04:10.450
and he came out on the other
side of some really dark times.

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:13.586
He still is who he is,
and that's why people are

00:04:13.686 --> 00:04:17.357
drawn to him, because
he has a story to tell.

00:04:17.457 --> 00:04:18.858
Justin: Yo.

00:04:18.958 --> 00:04:20.827
Can you buzz us in?

00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:21.995
[Buzzing]

00:04:24.730 --> 00:04:26.532
This was so shitty down here.

00:04:29.868 --> 00:04:31.671
Hailey: [Laughs]

00:04:31.771 --> 00:04:33.973
Scooter: You know, early on in
his career we'd always say,

00:04:34.073 --> 00:04:35.475
let's go for another one,
let's go for another one,

00:04:36.676 --> 00:04:37.977
another hit, another record,
another thing, another tour.

00:04:38.077 --> 00:04:40.546
Before "Purpose"
with "Journals,"

00:04:40.646 --> 00:04:42.315
I didn't want him to tour,
I wanted him to get healthy.

00:04:42.415 --> 00:04:44.517
And then he got healthy
and we went on "Purpose,"

00:04:44.617 --> 00:04:46.686
and then at the end he
was tired and said,

00:04:46.786 --> 00:04:47.754
look, I needed
a break again.

00:04:47.854 --> 00:04:48.821 line:0%
And we took
the break,

00:04:48.921 --> 00:04:50.323 line:0%
and he's taken a
very long break.

00:04:50.423 --> 00:04:52.058 line:0%
And in that time
he's found his wife.

00:04:52.158 --> 00:04:53.993
He's grown a lot.

00:04:54.093 --> 00:04:56.963
I don't put any pressure
on that timeline anymore.

00:04:57.063 --> 00:04:59.365
He's earned the right to
do it in his own time.

00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:01.434
Justin: I used to tell my
friends, because I was, like,

00:05:01.534 --> 00:05:06.572
ashamed that I lived in like
such a low poverty standards.

00:05:06.672 --> 00:05:08.074
I used to tell people, yeah,
there's a bowling alley

00:05:08.174 --> 00:05:09.509
downstairs and stuff.

00:05:09.609 --> 00:05:10.910
[Chuckles]

00:05:11.010 --> 00:05:13.646
It's booked, it's booked
up right now but...

00:05:13.746 --> 00:05:16.349
That's it...

00:05:16.449 --> 00:05:20.353
That's it.

00:05:20.453 --> 00:05:21.754
Hailey: Anything different?

00:05:21.854 --> 00:05:22.789
The floors?

00:05:22.889 --> 00:05:25.425
Justin: Yeah-ha.

00:05:25.525 --> 00:05:27.660
I think it was bigger.

00:05:27.760 --> 00:05:29.962
I don't think we ever showed
this in "Never Say Never,"

00:05:30.062 --> 00:05:32.465
but it was where I-- it was
the first apartment building

00:05:32.565 --> 00:05:35.835
where I lived here
for like 10 years.

00:05:35.935 --> 00:05:37.537
Brings back a lot of memories.

00:05:40.739 --> 00:05:41.808
Scooter: I remember the day
where he said he didn't

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:45.478
want to keep going, and
it was a very tough one.

00:05:45.578 --> 00:05:47.547
He just wanted to get away
and feel normal and needed

00:05:47.647 --> 00:05:49.482
a break from it all.

00:05:49.582 --> 00:05:53.353 line:0%
Allison: I freaked out, um,
when Justin canceled the tour.

00:05:53.453 --> 00:05:55.655 line:0%
Performing is the thing that
he loves most in this world,

00:05:55.755 --> 00:05:57.957
and so, for him to say that
he didn't want to do it,

00:05:58.057 --> 00:06:00.693
I knew it had to be
pretty serious.

00:06:00.793 --> 00:06:02.929 line:0%
Ryan: Having a constant
stimulation like that and

00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:06.933 line:0%
experiencing 50,000 people
chanting and just anywhere

00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:09.869
you go having all this
attention brought up, you know,

00:06:09.969 --> 00:06:12.071
your brain actually
gets worn out from that,

00:06:12.171 --> 00:06:14.374
where the standard
levels of Dopamine just

00:06:14.474 --> 00:06:16.609
don't get you
excited anymore.

00:06:16.709 --> 00:06:18.578
Allison: They have so
much fun, but it's also

00:06:18.678 --> 00:06:20.446
very isolating.

00:06:20.546 --> 00:06:23.149
And until you wake up in a
city and you don't remember

00:06:23.249 --> 00:06:26.786
where you are, you can't really
understand how hard it is.

00:06:26.886 --> 00:06:29.155
Justin: I think that
being human is,

00:06:29.255 --> 00:06:31.457
is challenging
for everybody.

00:06:31.557 --> 00:06:35.762
I think that we're all
struggling to some degree.

00:06:35.862 --> 00:06:38.798
We all have our individual
pains and fears

00:06:38.898 --> 00:06:42.435
and anxieties, worries.

00:06:42.535 --> 00:06:45.171
Ryan: There was a six-month
period where it was

00:06:45.271 --> 00:06:48.007
really tough for him,
really dark.

00:06:48.107 --> 00:06:51.544
I saw him in a lot of ways that
just really broke my heart.

00:06:51.644 --> 00:06:54.514
This last year at Coachella
when Ariana was headlining,

00:06:54.614 --> 00:06:56.916
she invited him to come up
and do a song with her.

00:06:57.016 --> 00:06:58.985
Anncr: Just one song--

00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:00.853
[Crowd cheering]

00:07:00.953 --> 00:07:02.188
Ryan: Justin was going back
and forth whether it was

00:07:02.288 --> 00:07:03.923
the right time or not.

00:07:04.023 --> 00:07:05.992
I think Scooter was thinking he
should have this opportunity

00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:07.860
to go out on that stage
so he could be reminded

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:10.763
himself of who he is and,
like, what he does.

00:07:10.863 --> 00:07:12.632
Ariana: I wasn't going to
bring any guests out tonight,

00:07:12.732 --> 00:07:15.168
but my friend Justin
Bieber came over...

00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:18.004
